Based on the provided specifications and guidelines, here is a complete Arduino sketch that implements the TensorFlow Lite Micro inference for an object classifier using the APDS9960 color sensor. The sketch includes all necessary initializations, data handling, and output processing as per the application requirements.

### Complete Sketch Code

```cpp
#include <Arduino.h>
#include <Wire.h>
#include <Adafruit_APDS9960.h>
#include "TensorFlowLite.h"
#include "tensorflow/lite/micro/all_ops_resolver.h"
#include "tensorflow/lite/micro/micro_error_reporter.h"
#include "tensorflow/lite/micro/micro_interpreter.h"

// Model files
#include "model.h"  // Replace with the actual path to your model header file

// Define the size of the tensor arena (in bytes)
constexpr int kTensorArenaSize = 4096;
uint8_t tensor_arena[kTensorArenaSize];

// Create an error reporter instance
tflite::MicroErrorReporter micro_error_reporter;
tflite::ErrorReporter* error_reporter = &micro_error_reporter;

// Create the model interpreter
const tflite::Model* model = tflite::GetModel(g_model);
if (model->version() != TFLITE_SCHEMA_VERSION) {
  error_reporter->Report("Model schema version does not match\nExpected: %d, Found: %d\n", 
                         TFLITE_SCHEMA_VERSION, model->version());
}

// Create an AllOpsResolver instance
tflite::AllOpsResolver resolver;

// Create a MicroInterpreter instance
tflite::MicroInterpreter interpreter(model, resolver, tensor_arena, kTensorArenaSize, error_reporter);

// Allocate memory for the tensors
TfLiteStatus allocate_status = interpreter.AllocateTensors();
if (allocate_status != kTfLiteOk) {
  error_reporter->Report("AllocateTensors() failed\n");
}

// Define the input and output pointers
TfLiteTensor* input_tensor = interpreter.input(0);
TfLiteTensor* output_tensor = interpreter.output(0);

// Initialize the APDS9960 sensor
Adafruit_APDS9960 apds;

void setup() {
  // Start serial communication
  Serial.begin(9600);
  while (!Serial) {
    delay(10);  // Wait for serial port to connect. Needed for native USB port only
  }

  // Initialize the APDS-9960 sensor
  if (apds.init()) {
    Serial.println("APDS-9960 initialization complete");
  } else {
    Serial.println("Something went wrong during APDS-9960 init!");
  }

  // Configure the sensor
  apds.enableColor(true);
}

void loop() {
  uint16_t r, g, b, c;

  if (apds.colorAvailable()) {
    // Read color data from the sensor
    apds.getColorData(&r, &g, &b, &c);

    // Normalize RGB values to range [0.0, 1.0]
    float red = static_cast<float>(r) / c;
    float green = static_cast<float>(g) / c;
    float blue = static_cast<float>(b) / c;

    // Ensure the values are within [0.0, 1.0]
    red = constrain(red, 0.0f, 1.0f);
    green = constrain(green, 0.0f, 1.0f);
    blue = constrain(blue, 0.0f, 1.0f);

    // Set the input tensor data
    input_tensor->data.f[0] = red;
    input_tensor->data.f[1] = green;
    input_tensor->data.f[2] = blue;

    // Run the inference
    TfLiteStatus invoke_status = interpreter.Invoke();
    if (invoke_status != kTfLiteOk) {
      error_reporter->Report("Invoke failed\n");
      return;
    }

    // Get the output tensor data
    uint8_t class_index = output_tensor->data.uint8[0];

    // Map the class index to the corresponding object class
    const char* object_class;
    switch (class_index) {
      case 0:
        object_class = "Apple";
        break;
      case 1:
        object_class = "Banana";
        break;
      case 2:
        object_class = "Orange";
        break;
      default:
        object_class = "Unknown";
        break;
    }

    // Output the result using Unicode emojis
    Serial.print("Detected: ");
    switch (class_index) {
      case 0:
        Serial.println("\U0001F34E");  // Apple emoji
        break;
      case 1:
        Serial.println("\U0001F34C");  // Banana emoji
        break;
      case 2:
        Serial.println("\U0001F34A");  // Orange emoji
        break;
      default:
        Serial.println("❓");          // Unknown emoji
        break;
    }
  }

  delay(500);  // Delay between readings
}
```

### Explanation of the Code

1. **Include Necessary Libraries**:
   - `Wire.h` and `Adafruit_APDS9960.h` for communication with the APDS-9960 sensor.
   - `TensorFlowLite.h` and related TFLite Micro headers for running the inference model.

2. **Define Tensor Arena**:
   - Allocate a tensor arena buffer of 4096 bytes to store intermediate activations during inference.

3. **Model Initialization**:
   - Load the pre-trained TensorFlow Lite model from `model.h`.
   - Use an `AllOpsResolver` to resolve all operators used in the model.
   - Create and initialize a `MicroInterpreter` with the model, operator resolver, tensor arena, and error reporter.
   - Allocate memory for tensors using the tensor arena.

4. **Sensor Initialization**:
   - Initialize the APDS-9960 color sensor and enable color data acquisition.

5. **Main Loop**:
   - Continuously check if new color data is available from the sensor.
   - Normalize RGB values to the range [0.0, 1.0].
   - Set the input tensor with normalized RGB values.
   - Run inference using `interpreter.Invoke()`.
   - Retrieve the output tensor and map the class index to the corresponding object class name.
   - Print the detected object class using Unicode emojis.

### Notes
- Ensure that the model file (`model.h`) is correctly included in your project.
- The APDS-9960 sensor initialization and data reading functions are assumed to work as expected. If you encounter issues, refer to the Adafruit library documentation.
- Adjust the delay between readings as needed based on your application requirements.

This sketch should be uploaded to your Arduino Nano 33 BLE Sense board for running object classification using RGB color sensor inputs.

